topic_description: Please conduct this session AFTER you have done the stress assessment.
question:
Please look at your results from the stress assessment (spider) and identify the area where you experience most stress. What do you think are the reasons for the stress in this area? What would help you to alleviate this stress?

Please elaborate in at least 10 sentences.
reflection_snapshot:
Je crois que je ne suis pas quelqu'un de stressé dans la vie en général. Sur l'araignée, c'est le stress interpersonnel et celui de tous les jours qui paraissent les plus dominants. Je dois honnêtement dire que c'est le cas simplement parce que par rapport aux autres catégories j'ai répondu plus haut mais toujours faible. Ce qui revient à dire que je ne suis pas très stressée à propos de ça non plus. Si je dois absolument trouver une source de stress je pense que je devrais dire que ma timidité peut parfois générer du stress. Mais ce stress ne dure que très peu de temps, quand il s'agit d'une présentation, il commence en entrant dans la salle et s'arrête directement à la fin de celle ci. S'il s'agit d'un interaction avec quelqu'un, il faut seulement un temps d'adaptation, après ce dernier, tout roule et le stress disparait. 
Pour atténuer ce stress quasiment inexistant, je fais en sorte de me préparer mentalement à la situation générant le stress et cela fonctionne en général plutôt bien
suggestion_content: C'est super que tu prennes le temps de réfléchir à ton stress et d'identifier les sources ! Pour aller plus loin, pourrais-tu explorer comment ta timidité influence tes interactions au quotidien ? Quelles stratégies spécifiques pourrais-tu mettre en place pour te sentir plus à l'aise dans ces situations ?
final_reflection:
Je crois que je ne suis pas quelqu'un de stressé dans la vie en général. Sur l'araignée, c'est le stress interpersonnel et celui de tous les jours qui paraissent les plus dominants. Je dois honnêtement dire que c'est le cas simplement parce que par rapport aux autres catégories j'ai répondu plus haut mais toujours faible. Ce qui revient à dire que je ne suis pas très stressée à propos de ça non plus. Si je dois absolument trouver une source de stress je pense que je devrais dire que ma timidité peut parfois générer du stress. Mais ce stress ne dure que très peu de temps, quand il s'agit d'une présentation, il commence en entrant dans la salle et s'arrête directement à la fin de celle ci. S'il s'agit d'un interaction avec quelqu'un, il faut seulement un temps d'adaptation, après ce dernier, tout roule et le stress disparait. 
Pour atténuer ce stress quasiment inexistant, je fais en sorte de me préparer mentalement à la situation générant le stress et cela fonctionne en général plutôt bien. 
Après, ce n'est pas du tout un stress handicapant qui fait perdre la mémoire ou autre, il n'influence réellement que très peu ma personne. A la limite il me donne un peu chaud et me fais parler beaucoup (j'ai tendance à évacuer le stress en parlant beaucoup) ou me donne la bougeotte.

topic_description: Co-creation: Skills and motivation to build, develop and facilitate collaborative relationships with diverse stakeholders, characterised by psychological safety and genuine co-creation.
question: Think about this week’s group experience together with your peers. What role did you take in the group? Is this the role you usually take? How do you feel about it?
reflection_snapshot: I took the role of creative thinker and idea generator. Usually I am rather in the role of leader and pacemaker, setting up the targets, the structure and the pace to ensure that targets will be achieved. The creative thinker / idea generator role gives me more possibilities to connect with myself and to have deep thoughts rather than being driven by externalities. In one sense, it's much more rewarding.
suggestion_content: Great job on identifying your role as a creative thinker! It’s fantastic that you found it rewarding. To deepen your reflection, consider how this role impacted your group dynamics. What specific ideas did you contribute, and how did they influence the group’s outcome?
final_reflection: I took the role of creative thinker and idea generator. Usually I am rather in the role of leader and pacemaker, setting up the targets, the structure and the pace to ensure that targets will be achieved. The creative thinker / idea generator role gives me more possibilities to connect with myself and to have deep thoughts rather than being driven by externalities. In one sense, it's much more rewarding.

topic_description:
Overview

Case Clinic is a peer coaching process designed to identify innovative solutions and next steps for addressing a pressing and immediate leadership challenge. In a Case Clinic, a case giver presents a case, and peers or team members act as coaches.

Application

This peer-learning process can be used to address challenges where the case giver is the main decision maker. It can build a high level of trust and positive energy among a peer group and can be combined with contemplative and listening practices for maximum effect.

Principles

• Be specific. The case should present a (sustainability-related) leadership challenge that is current and concrete.

• Include a decision maker. The case giver needs to be a key decision maker in the case.

• Reinforce peer relationships. The participants in the Case Clinics are peers, so there is no hierarchical relationship.

• Practice listening. Coaches don’t give advice; instead they listen deeply.
question: What are your 1-3 personal takeaways from the entire peer coaching experience (considering both roles as a coach and as a coachee)? What can you concretely integrate in your day-to-day life?
reflection_snapshot:
1- We are starting the sustainability transition but the next generations will have to get it over the finish line. Therefore education plays a crucial role.
2- It is important to know what our own individual values and to have a North Star to navigate among the expectations from the outside world (family, society, corporate and so on)
3- With regards to sustainability transition, I have to understand what are the compromises and trade-offs I am accepting and then align my behaviour with them.

I am already integrating the educational aspect in my daily life with my two daughters.
suggestion_content: Great job on identifying key takeaways from your peer coaching experience! To deepen your reflection, consider exploring how your values influence your daily decisions. What specific actions can you take to align your behavior with your understanding of sustainability? This could enhance your insights even further!
final_reflection:
1- We are starting the sustainability transition but the next generations will have to get it over the finish line. Therefore education plays a crucial role.
2- It is important to know what our own individual values and to have a North Star to navigate among the expectations from the outside world (family, society, corporate and so on)
3- With regards to sustainability transition, I have to understand what are the compromises and trade-offs I am accepting and then align my behaviour with them.

I am already integrating the educational aspect in my daily life with my two daughters.

suggestion_content: It's great to see you engaging with your experiences! However, your reflection could benefit from more depth. What specific challenges did you face, and how did they change your perspective? Exploring these questions can help you uncover valuable insights about yourself.
final_reflection:
There was one time i recall very clearly where i stepped out of my comfort zone.
We were doing our usual lecture in microeconomics when the professor, explaining an economic principle, asked us students who was willing to sing in front of everyone.
I thought to myself: "i remember the lyrics of my favourite song, why shouldn't I?". Eventually i got in front of everyone and even though i was very anxious everybody clapped and was enthusiast of my performance.
From this experience i can safely say that stepping out of my comfort zone is a really exciting thing to do, i can always learn by doing so in my everyday life.

topic_description:
Welcome to a new week, this time with the theme of “Learning Techniques & Self-Organisation”, the ability to effectively acquire, retain, and apply new knowledge or skills through various methods and strategies and to to manage your time, tasks, and resources efficiently to achieve personal or professional goals in an orderly manner.

We will reflect on the previous week, learn about the theme and plan the week ahead.

Why are there themed reflections?

Your innovative study program is aware of the importance of Inner Development in your Education and has decided to offer you Rflect to help you practice those Inner Competencies.

Inner Competences (some call it soft skills, personal development, etc.) are based on your thoughts, feelings, and behaviors. These competencies shape how we manage ourselves, relate to others, and respond to challenges. They are key to personal development, emotional well-being, and success in both personal and professional spheres. You can find out why there are important here.

Rflect helps you practice inner competencies outlined in the Inner Development Goals (IDG) and beyond.

Every week you will have one topic where you reflect on your personal learning journey and also on 1 of the 23 competencies outlined in the IDG Framework.

For the first semester(s) we will introduce those competencies broadly to you (with a few reflective questions). Later on, we will dive deeper into them and practice them with exercises and actions.
question: The theme of this week is 'Learning Techniques & Self-Organisation'. How is this topic relevant for yourself?
reflection_snapshot: Da ich extrem viele Lebensinhalte nebeneinander habe, muss ich mich jede Woche mit der Organisation der einzelnen Bereiche auseinandersetzen. Habe ich die Woche gut durchdacht, mir überlegt, wann ich was mache und mich auch in gewissen Aktivitäten limitiert, erleichtert mir das die Tage während der Woche enorm. Lernstrategien habe ich noch nicht so viele verschiedene angewendet, ausser viel Fleiss und Repetition.
suggestion_content: Es ist großartig, dass du dir Gedanken über deine Organisation und Lernstrategien machst! Um deine Reflexion zu vertiefen, könntest du überlegen: Was genau hat dir in der Vergangenheit bei der Organisation geholfen? Welche neuen Lerntechniken könntest du ausprobieren, um deine Strategien zu erweitern?
final_reflection: Da ich extrem viele Lebensinhalte nebeneinander habe, muss ich mich jede Woche mit der Organisation der einzelnen Bereiche auseinandersetzen. Habe ich die Woche gut durchdacht, mir überlegt, wann ich was mache und mich auch in gewissen Aktivitäten limitiert, erleichtert mir das die Tage während der Woche enorm. Ich arbeite da vor allem mit meinem Google Calender, verschiedenen Farben und bewusst gesetzten "Lernblöcken". Zudem versuche ich Regelmässigkeiten zu erhalten und mir genug Schlaf, Freizeit bewusst einzuplanen.   Lernstrategien habe ich noch nicht so viele verschiedene angewendet, ausser viel Fleiss und Repetition.

reflection_snapshot: Ich habe erneut erkannt, dass gewisse Module mehr Überwindung / Motivation benötigen, um dem Stoff aufmerksam zu folgen. In Zukunft möchte ich meine Problemfächer mit grösserem Enthusiasmus angehen.

question:
What would you like others to know or do better when working with you? Similarly, what can you do better when working together with others?

Have you told them? Why yes / no?
reflection_snapshot: Che apprezzo il lavoro di tutti, tuttavia a volte è difficile
suggestion_content: Il tuo testo mostra un apprezzamento per il lavoro di squadra, il che è fantastico! Tuttavia, per migliorare la tua riflessione, potresti approfondire le difficoltà che incontri e come potresti comunicare meglio queste esigenze agli altri. Prova a scrivere un po' di più sui tuoi sentimenti e le tue esperienze.
final_reflection: I appreciate everyone's work; however, sometimes it’s challenging to align my way of working with others. There are times when they start with a fixed idea and there isn’t much flexibility, but often things change and need to be adjusted, and we need to be ready to embrace these changes. Generally, we could benefit from having more trust in each other's abilities. I could make an effort to better communicate my expectations and ideas.

question: What made you pick this number? Is there anything you would like to change?
reflection_snapshot: J'ai choisi ce chiffre, car il est à un niveau que je considère correspondre à mon implication dans mes études, je pourrais en revanche la rendre encore plus importante. Par exemple, je voudrais arriver à anticiper encore plus les travaux à rendre, mais dans les temps qui viennent je voudrais surtout arriver à anticiper les partiels, car le temps passe plus vite que ce que l'on pense. J'aimerais également arriver à mieux préparer mes cours avant d'y aller.
suggestion_content: C'est super que tu prennes le temps de réfléchir à ton implication dans tes études ! Pour approfondir ta réflexion, pourquoi penses-tu qu’anticiper les partiels est si important pour toi ? Quelles stratégies pourrais-tu mettre en place pour mieux préparer tes cours ?
final_reflection:
J'ai choisi ce chiffre, car il est à un niveau que je considère correspondre à mon implication dans mes études, je pourrais en revanche la rendre encore plus importante. Par exemple, je voudrais arriver à anticiper encore plus les travaux à rendre, mais dans les temps qui viennent je voudrais surtout arriver à anticiper les partiels, car le temps passe plus vite que ce que l'on pense. J'aimerais également arriver à mieux préparer mes cours avant d'y aller. 
Anticiper les partiels m'est important pour ne pas me retrouver submergé à devoir réviser tout mon semestre à quelques jours de l'examen, ce qui serait infaisable pour les réussir au mieux. Je voudrais aussi me donner de bonnes chances en avance pour le deuxième semestre, qui sera une moyenne des deux. 
Pour préparer mieux mes cours, il faudrait que je relise les précédents avant d'y aller, mais aussi que je les mette bien au propre et que je vérifie que tout soit au clair dans ma tête au cas où j'aurais des questions à poser.

question: Looking back at the start, how are you proceeding with your 1-3 personal learning goals?
reflection_snapshot: Je pense que je m'avance bien dans les objectifs que je me suis fixé au début. Ils étaient assez globaux mais pour autant deux d'entre eux sont en bonne voie, le dernier aussi selon moi, même si seul la fin du semestre pourra nous le dire.
suggestion_content: C'est super que tu penses avancer dans tes objectifs ! Pour approfondir ta réflexion, pourrais-tu expliquer comment tu mesures tes progrès pour chacun de tes objectifs ? Qu'est-ce qui te fait dire que tu es sur la bonne voie ? Cela pourrait vraiment enrichir ton analyse.
final_reflection:
Je pense que je m'avance bien dans les objectifs que je me suis fixé au début. Ils étaient assez globaux mais pour autant deux d'entre eux sont en bonne voie, le dernier aussi selon moi, même si seul la fin du semestre pourra nous le dire. 
La mesure de mes progrès est simple, je discute avec de plus en plus de monde à IBM24, ce qui est un avancement majeur, on est en train de se créer un réseau qui potentiellement peut durer toute une vie. En ce qui concerne l'autre, j'ai moins besoin de réfléchir avant de prononcer une phrase en allemand. Hier, j'étais à EuropaPark en Allemagne, par conséquent j'ai du parler allemand, et j'ai moins de mal à retrouver mon vocabulaire qu'avant et les mots sortent plus naturellement.

question: What is a highlight from the last 4 weeks that you would like to remember 1 year from now?
reflection_snapshot: Je pense que le souvenir que j'aimerais garder de ces quatre premières semaines reste la semaine d'intégration dont je suis sûre de me souvenir encore dans un an. Cette semaine nous avait permis d'en apprendre plus sur chaque personne suivant le cursus IBM, mais aussi sur les différences de nos cultures et langages. J'ai trouvé passionnant d'échanger nos expressions du quotidien qui ne font pas partie de nos savoirs. Je pense que les échanges interculturelles que nous pratiquons depuis un mois ont influencé effectivement ma vision du monde dans le sens où maintenant, à chaque fois que je fais quelque chose je me demande comment les autres le verrait si pour moi c'est naturel et inversement. Je pense que ça m'a aussi rendue plus indulgente auprès d'inconnu, ça m'a rappelé qu'on ne connaît pas les gens avant de discuter réellement avec eux. Comme le dit une citation que j'aime beaucoup "Tous les gens que tu rencontres mènent un combat dont tu ignores tout. Sois indulgente. Toujours". ça me rappelle que nous n'avons pas tous le même parcours ou les mêmes expériences de vie et que tous le monde n'a pas la même perception des choses en général, ni la même perception d'une réussite.
suggestion_content: C'est super que tu aies pris le temps de réfléchir à ton expérience d'intégration ! Quelles situations spécifiques te viennent à l'esprit où tu as appliqué cette nouvelle perspective ?

Cette semaine nous avait permis d'en apprendre plus sur chaque personne suivant le cursus IBM, mais aussi sur les différences de nos cultures et langages. J'ai trouvé passionnant d'échanger nos expressions du quotidien qui ne font pas partie de nos savoirs. Je pense que les échanges interculturelles que nous pratiquons depuis un mois ont influencé effectivement ma vision du monde dans le sens où maintenant, à chaque fois que je fais quelque chose je me demande comment les autres le verrait si pour moi c'est naturel et inversement. Je pense que ça m'a aussi rendue plus indulgente auprès d'inconnu, ça m'a rappelé qu'on ne connaît pas les gens avant de discuter réellement avec eux. Comme le dit une citation que j'aime beaucoup "Tous les gens que tu rencontres mènent un combat dont tu ignores tout. Sois indulgente. Toujours". ça me rappelle que nous n'avons pas tous le même parcours ou les mêmes expériences de vie et que tous le monde n'a pas la même perception des choses en général, ni la même perception d'une réussite.

question: What core values or principles do you believe are most important in guiding your actions and decision-making during your educational journey? How do these values relate to the "good of the whole" or the broader community?
reflection_snapshot:
I frequently engage in introspection regarding my core values. Despite remaining uncertain, I have discovered that excessive reflection can impede sound judgment. In order to gain clarity, I completed the LifeValues Inventory, which served to reaffirm a number of values that I had already identified. My dedication to sustainability, environmental consciousness, and equality motivates me to improve the world for both humans and nature. These values constitute the bedrock of my approach to life and have consistently been of paramount importance alongside my dedication to fitness.

However, with regard to my educational trajectory, I have identified a set of values that serve to inform and direct my actions and decision-making in a more specific manner. These values are accuracy, expertise, courage, and perfection.

Accuracy is of paramount importance, as I endeavour to conduct my research and assignments with precision and meticulous attention to detail. Such a commitment ensures that my contributions are trustworthy and reliable, which I believe is essential for personal and academic integrity. This is consistent with the notion of the "good of the whole", as accuracy provides a foundation of truth, benefiting all those who rely on credible information.

Expertise also plays a significant role. I am dedicated to furthering my knowledge and comprehension of my field, striving to attain mastery of the subject matter I am studying. This pursuit of expertise is not merely a personal endeavour; it is also about making valuable contributions to my academic and professional communities. In my view, expertise facilitates informed decision-making that can have a beneficial impact on the wider community.

The virtue of courage can be defined as the capacity to overcome one's natural reluctance to confront challenges, to embrace the potential for learning and growth that arises from mistakes, and to persevere in the face of adversity. In an educational context, this signifies a willingness to receive feedback and engage with challenging topics. The capacity for courage enables innovation and progress, which are beneficial not only to the individual but also to the broader community, as they encourage a mindset of growth and adaptation.

While perfection can be a double-edged sword, it motivates me to maintain high standards. I endeavour to achieve the highest standards in my academic work, continually challenging myself to exceed my current limits. Although perfectionism can occasionally result in excessive preoccupation with details, it also motivates a dedication to producing work that I can be proud of, thereby making a positive contribution to group projects, collaborations, and the academic community as a whole.

These values inform not only my actions but also my engagement with the broader community. They ensure that my contributions are accurate, well-informed, courageous, and held to high standards, with the aim of benefiting not only my individual success but also positively impacting the environments and communities of which I am a part.
suggestion_content: You've done a great job articulating your core values and how they guide your educational journey! To deepen your reflection, consider exploring how these values have shaped specific experiences or decisions. How have moments of courage or the pursuit of accuracy influenced your learning?
final_reflection:
I frequently engage in introspection regarding my core values, though this was not always the case. In my formative years, I did not devote much attention to the notion of core values. I was not instructed to do so, and I predominantly relied on intuitive judgments. On occasion, I would engage in profound reflection on specific values. However, it was not until my mid-20s that I began to contemplate them in a more serious manner. This shift occurred gradually, driven by my aspiration to ascertain the fundamental values that guide my actions. The completion of tools such as the LifeValues Inventory has facilitated the identification and consolidation of my guiding principles.

The values that emerged were those that I had always sensed were important, namely concern for the environment, particularly sustainability, and equality, which aim to make the world a better place for both humans and nature. These values, in conjunction with fitness, constitute the bedrock of my daily existence. However, in the context of my educational journey, other values have assumed greater significance: accuracy, expertise, courage, and perfection. It has become evident that these values play an instrumental role in influencing my approach to learning, personal growth and engagement with the broader community.

The value of accuracy is particularly salient, as I am continually engaged in the evaluation of the trustworthiness and completeness of the information I encounter. I pose the following question to myself: The question thus arises as to the veracity of the information in question. Does my perspective, which is predominantly European, represent the only valid viewpoint, or can it be complemented by the inclusion of other perspectives, particularly those that are less vocal, such as the poor, the silent, animals, or nature, particularly in discussions about sustainability? This value encourages me to pursue a more comprehensive understanding that can contribute to the greater good by incorporating perspectives that are frequently marginalised.

Expertise has become a fundamental aspect of my educational trajectory, as I aspire to provide a level of assistance that extends beyond mere general support. My objective is to facilitate the integration of diverse and well-researched perspectives into discourse. The development of expertise enables meaningful contributions to be made to academic and professional discussions, offering insights that can positively influence the decisions of the community.

The courage to venture into uncharted territories and embrace the possibility of making mistakes is a crucial aspect of the journey of knowledge. My approach frequently entails the examination of novel avenues, the enhancement of my comprehension through the perusal of literature, the pursuit of academic studies, and the acquisition of real-world experiences. Although I would not necessarily identify myself as a "trailblazer," I do take pride in being someone who seeks out new paths to enhance my knowledge, ultimately benefiting the community by introducing innovative ideas.

My passion for my chosen fields motivates me to pursue excellence and maintain the highest standards. This motivates me to apply my best effort to academic work, with the goal of achieving excellence. Nevertheless, I am conscious that pursuing perfection can be arduous in the context of an increasingly intricate world. While striving for perfection and accuracy is undoubtedly valuable, it can occasionally impede progress when navigating the nuances of one's studies. Despite my experience of agile methodologies, I find myself experiencing difficulty in relinquishing these ideals when faced with ambiguity.

In conclusion, my core values have not only informed my educational trajectory but have also shaped my engagement with the world. While they can present challenges, particularly when striving for perfection and accuracy encounters the complexities of reality, they also provide a robust foundation for informed and courageous decision-making. My objective is to ensure that my educational journey contributes positively to a broader community, promoting a more accurate, expert, and inclusive understanding of the world we all inhabit.

In conclusion, my core values have not only informed my educational trajectory but have also shaped my engagement with the world. While they can present challenges, particularly when striving for perfection and accuracy encounters the complexities of reality, they also provide a robust foundation for informed and courageous decision-making. My objective is to ensure that my educational journey contributes positively to a broader community, promoting a more accurate, expert, and inclusive understanding of the world we all inhabit.

topic_description:
Du begibst dich auf eine spannende Reise im Rahmen des Moduls / CAS Leadership & Persönlichkeitsentwicklung. Mitten im Leben und doch am Start. Zeit für kurz inne zu halten und dich mit der aktuellen Situation zu beschäftigen.

Zum Start hast du die Situationsanalyse aus dem Tool Profolio erstellt. Nachfolgend Fragen dazu und zum Start deines Learning Journey.
question: Welche Themen bewegen mich nach der Situationsanalyse?
suggestion_content: Es ist toll, dass du dich mit der Situationsanalyse auseinandersetzt! Um deine Reflexion zu vertiefen, könntest du mehr über deine Gefühle und Gedanken zu den Themen schreiben, die dich bewegen. Was genau hat dich in der Analyse überrascht oder zum Nachdenken angeregt?
final_reflection:
Ich habe gemerkt, wie wichtig es ist, regelmässig innezuhalten und zu überlegen, wo ich gerade stehe. Diese Analyse zeigt mir, wo ich in meinem Leben stehe und was ich noch verbessern kann. Dabei wurde geschaut, was ich beruflich mache, wie ich mich entwickeln kann und wie die Arbeitsbedingungen sind.
Ich habe erkannt, dass ich mich beruflich noch weiterentwickeln und meine Laufbahn aktiv gestalten kann. Das motiviert mich, meine Karriereziele klarer zu definieren und daran zu arbeiten, sie zu erreichen. Die Standortbestimmung zeigt mir, dass ich mich mit meiner Arbeit identifiziere. Aber ich habe auch erkannt, dass ich mehr Erfüllung finden könnte, wenn ich mehr auf meine Bedürfnisse und Werte achte.
Auch mein Privatleben und mein Wohlbefinden wurden bewertet. Sie hat mir gezeigt, dass ich in meinen Beziehungen und in meiner Freizeit zufrieden bin. Aber ich könnte noch mehr tun, um eine bessere Balance zwischen Arbeit und Erholung zu finden. Ich sollte mir mehr Zeit für mich nehmen.
Ich muss lernen, besser mit Stress umzugehen. Pausen sind wichtig, um gesund und produktiv zu bleiben.
Die Persönlichkeitsdimension hat mir gezeigt, wie wichtig es ist, sich selbst zu vertrauen und die eigenen Stärken zu nutzen. Man muss lernen, "Nein" zu sagen und sich abzugrenzen. Das ist wichtig, um nicht überfordert zu werden.

Ich habe gelernt, dass ich viele Stärken habe. Und ich weiss jetzt, was ich noch lernen muss, um mich weiterzuentwickeln.

topic_description:
Dear Student,

Welcome to the Rflect journey that will accompany your Leading the Sustainability Transition IEMBA course!

You are invited to embark on this “self-leadership for sustainability” journey alongside the course contents in order to help you personalize the learning experience, and make sure you get the most out of it for your own learning, rather than doing it ‘just’ to pass the course. You will train key future skills such as self-awareness, metacognition and perspective taking which are in key demand for any sustainability-fit leader.

The content of your reflections will not be graded, but your commitment to your reflection process is an essential part of your learning experience. Note that all reflections marked ‘private’ will not be visible to anyone, so the more honest you are with yourself, the better your learning outcomes will be. You may also want to make use of your personal reflections to enhance your reflection paper.

You receive questions in English, but you can answer in your preferred language - except those shared with the lecturer and the class that can be answered in English (class) or German (lecturer only).

All the best and see you soon!
question: This module has generic learning goals for all of its students. You as an individual have your own reasons for being here. What are your 2-3 personal learning goals?
reflection_snapshot:
I want to be able to 
-confidently educate different type of stakeholders about the relevance, importance  and opportunities to implement sustainability principles and mindset in business units, 
-make sustainability a priority in a profit-driven culture, next to high growth targets in a short-term thinking environment, highlighting the business value
-gain insights on new tools, frameworks, best practice from my cohort, guest speaker and lecturer and be able to apply them

Gain new insights on how to transition to circular models, especially in large B-to-B enterprises? (mitigating known challenges and barriers)
suggestion_content: Great job outlining your personal learning goals! To deepen your reflection, consider exploring how you plan to overcome specific challenges in implementing sustainability principles. What strategies will you use to engage stakeholders effectively in a profit-driven culture? This could add valuable depth to your insights.

-make sustainability a priority in a profit-driven culture, next to high growth targets in a short-term thinking environment, highlighting the business value
-gain insights on new tools, frameworks, best practice from my cohort, guest speaker and lecturer and be able to apply them

Gain new insights on how to transition to circular models, especially in large B-to-B enterprises? (mitigating known challenges and barriers)

topic_description: Halte deine anfänglichen Erwartungen fest und definieren deine Lernziele, um den Grundstein für deine Lernreise zu legen.
question: Stell dir vor, das Studium ist zu Ende und du blickst zufrieden auf deine Studienzeit zurück. Woran erkennst du, ob es ein Erfolg für dich war? Was hast du gelernt/verändert/erreicht?
reflection_snapshot:
Ich kenne Tools/Interventionen zur Gestaltung von Workshops (Einbezug der MA)
Die ersten Schritte in einem Change Projekt werden mir klarer. 
Ich baue in meinen Projekten mehr Interventionen ein. 
Vor dem Start eines Projektes nutze ich vermehrt "Appreciative Inquiry" um die Werte des ggü zu verstehen 
Ich habe gute Tools für die wichtige Auftragsklärung 
Ich suche mir vermehrt Multiplikatoren/Change Agents. 
Konflikten trete ich entspannt entgegen und nutze sie als Chancen, ungesagtes sichtbar zu machen.
suggestion_content: Es ist großartig zu sehen, wie du konkrete Werkzeuge und Ansätze für deine Projekte identifiziert hast! Um deine Reflexion zu vertiefen, frage dich: Wie haben diese neuen Erkenntnisse deine Herangehensweise an Veränderungen beeinflusst? Was war ein spezifisches Beispiel, wo du diese Tools erfolgreich eingesetzt hast?
final_reflection:
Ich kenne Tools/Interventionen zur Gestaltung von Workshops (Einbezug der MA)
Die ersten Schritte in einem Change Projekt werden mir klar - ich packe es mutig an.  
Ich baue in meinen Projekten mehr Interventionen ein und freue mich auf den (kritischen) Austausch mit den Betroffenen. 
Vor dem Start eines Projektes nutze ich vermehrt "Appreciative Inquiry" um die Werte des ggü zu verstehen und eine positive Zukunft zu gestalten. 
Ich habe gute Tools für die wichtige Auftragsklärung 
Ich suche mir vermehrt Multiplikatoren/Change Agents. 
Konflikten trete ich entspannt entgegen und nutze sie als Chancen, ungesagtes sichtbar zu machen.

question: Was waren bis jetzt Deine 1-3 wichtigsten Erkenntnisse aus dem CAS und/oder Deiner vergangenen Wochen für Deine persönliche Entwicklung? Was macht diese Ideen/Einsichten für Dich und Deine (zukünftige) Karriere bedeutsam?
reflection_snapshot:
1   Erkenntnis | Absprachen im Team, wie kommuniziert wird und wie man miteinander umgeht. Dies erspart Diskussionen und schafft Klarheit. Diese schriftlich festhalten und immer wieder anpassen.

2  Erkenntnis | Wie wichtig es ist, eine gute Lern-Atmosphäre zu schaffen oder Einstieg in eine solche.

3  Wie werden sich die Berufe, in denen ich unterrichte, in Zukunft verändern? Wie kann ich meinen Unterricht darauf ausrichten und meine Lernenden darauf vorbereiten? Diese Frage hängt im Raum.
suggestion_content: Es ist großartig, dass du dir bereits Gedanken über deine wichtigsten Erkenntnisse machst! Um deine Reflexion zu vertiefen, könntest du überlegen, wie genau die Kommunikation im Team deine persönliche Entwicklung beeinflusst hat. Was bedeutet eine gute Lern-Atmosphäre für dich konkret?
final_reflection:
1   Erkenntnis | Absprachen im Team, wie kommuniziert wird und wie man miteinander umgeht. Dies erspart Diskussionen und schafft Klarheit. Diese schriftlich festhalten und immer wieder anpassen.

2  Erkenntnis | Für das Lernsetting ist es wichtig, eine gute Lern-Atmosphäre zu schaffen.

topic_description:
NEW DEADLINE: We have listened :). Based on your feedback during the Oct 22 workshop, the new deadline for these reflections is Sunday 12h so you can schedule when you have most headspace to do these reflections well.

Welcome to a new week, this time with the theme of “Listening & Dialogues”, the competence to listen and engage in dialogues involves actively understanding others' perspectives, fostering open communication, and creating a collaborative environment for meaningful exchange.

We will reflect on the previous week, learn about the theme and plan the week ahead.

Why are there themed reflections?

Your innovative study program is aware of the importance of Inner Development in your Education and has decided to offer you Rflect to help you practice those Inner Competencies.

Inner Competences (some call it soft skills, personal development, etc.) are based on your thoughts, feelings, and behaviors. These competencies shape how we manage ourselves, relate to others, and respond to challenges. They are key to personal development, emotional well-being, and success in both personal and professional spheres. You can find out why there are important here.

Rflect helps you practice inner competencies outlined in the Inner Development Goals (IDG) and beyond.

Every week you will have one topic where you reflect on your personal learning journey and also on 1 of the 23 competencies outlined in the IDG Framework.

topic_description:
In dieser Peer-Coaching-Sitzung werdet ihr in Dreiergruppen zusammenkommen, um einander dabei zu helfen, das bisher Gelernte zu verstehen und eure Führungsziele zu überlegen.

Die folgende Leit-Fragen könnt ihr nutzen.

  1. Führung und Strategische Ziele:

    • Welche Führungsziele verfolgst du aktuell oder welche möchtest du erreichen?

    • Wie möchtest du durch deine Führung zur Weiterentwicklung und Innovation in deinem Team oder deiner Organisation, besonders in der Technologiebranche, beitragen?

    • Mit welchen besonderen Herausforderungen rechnest du als Frau in einer Führungsposition in der Technologiebranche, und wie planst du, diese zu bewältigen?

  2. Integration des Gelernten:

    • Welche Führungskompetenzen oder Erkenntnisse aus dem Programm hast du bereits in deiner Rolle umgesetzt, und wie haben sie deine Herangehensweise verändert?

    • Wie möchtest du das Feedback aus dieser Peer-Coaching-Sitzung nutzen, um deine Führungskompetenzen weiterzuentwickeln?

    • Welche Schritte wirst du unternehmen, um in deinem Führungsstil weiterhin zu wachsen?
question: Beschreibe kurz deine Erfahrung mit Peer-Coaching. Beschreibe in wenigen Sätzen, was gut funktioniert hat und was nicht, während du jede der drei Rollen innehattest.
reflection_snapshot:
Beobachterin:
Spannende Aufgabe, zu sehen, wie mit gezielter Fragestellung des Coachs herausgeschält werden konnte, was eigentlich schon lange Entschieden aber nicht bewusst war.

Coachee
Ich konnte durch die gute Fragestellungen des Coaches während des Antwortens direkt reflektieren. Diese Erfahrung war für mich neu und wertvoll (ich selber hatte noch nie ein Coaching). 

Coach
Ich hatte anfangs etwas bedenken, ob ich die richtigen Frage zur Unterstützung des Coachees stellen kann. Merkte aber im Verlaufe des Gesprächs, dass dies von alleine passiert, sobald man aktiv zuhört und neugierig/interessiert ist. Teilweise hatte ich etwas Mühe einzuschätzen, wann ich den Coachee unterbrechen darf, um eine Frage zu stellen. Merkte aber, dass man mit der Zeit auch hier das Gegenüber einschätzen kann und den richtigen Zeitpunkt findet.
Auch wertvoll war für mich, dass Gehörte zusammenzufassen und dann vom Coachee nochmals bestätigen zu lassen. Dies gibt beiden Seiten die Sicherheit, sich richtig verstanden zu haben.
suggestion_content: Dein Text zeigt bereits eine gute Reflexion über deine Erfahrungen im Peer-Coaching, und ich finde es toll, wie du die verschiedenen Rollen beschrieben hast! Um deine Reflexion zu vertiefen, könntest du darüber nachdenken, wie du dich in jeder Rolle gefühlt hast. Was hat dich am meisten überrascht oder herausgefordert?
final_reflection:
Beobachterin:
Spannende Aufgabe, zu sehen, wie mit gezielter Fragestellung des Coachs herausgeschält werden konnte, was eigentlich schon lange Entschieden aber nicht bewusst war.

question: Consider a time when you were pushed out of your comfort zone in a learning environment. How did this experience affect your mindset toward future challenges?
reflection_snapshot:
One notable experience that challenged me beyond my comfort zone in a learning environment was during a systemic training course I undertook 2017. At the time, I considered it to be one of the most valuable educational experiences I had ever encountered, but it also presented some of the most significant challenges. The subjects we studied, particularly those related to mindset, attitude and systemic thinking, required a high level of intellectual engagement. Although I was able to grasp the questioning frameworks and techniques with relative ease, I found it challenging to fully internalise the required mindset.

During the course, I found it challenging to apply these abstract concepts in a meaningful way. The difficulty did not lie in the structure of the questions, which I could readily reproduce, but in adopting the more profound systemic perspective that the course emphasised. At times, I felt overwhelmed by the intricacies of shifting my mindset, and I was left with the impression that I had not fully grasped the impact of what I had learned by the time the course ended.

However, this discomfort prompted me to continue my research. Following the course, I engaged in a period of continuous reflection, reading a range of books and experimenting with different real-world scenarios for over a year to fully internalise the lessons. I came to understand that the learning process did not end with the training programme; it continued as I applied, tested and adapted the concepts in my daily work activities. With time, the systemic approach became more evident, and I developed a greater understanding of how mindset affects our responses and decisions in complex situations.

One of the initial challenges I faced during the course was that I had been sent by my boss with no background, and I lacked a robust support system for reflection and exchange. This experience highlighted the value of having dedicated time and space to discuss and process new ideas. As a result, I now adopt a different approach to future challenges. I have developed a more structured approach to framing and reflecting on situations, often beginning with agile tools such as the 5 Whys. This tool enables me to ascertain the most appropriate approach to challenges before embarking on them, to analyse my performance during the process, and to reflect on the lessons I can learn from them afterwards.

In hindsight, this experience has fundamentally altered my perspective on learning and growth. It demonstrated that discomfort is frequently a prerequisite to genuine, enduring comprehension, and that the insights we seek may require time to emerge. This has provided me with greater patience and resilience when facing complex, unfamiliar challenges. I have also learned to trust that, even if I do not immediately grasp everything, continued reflection and experimentation will eventually lead to greater clarity.

Go Deeper subsequently inquired about practical applications of systemic thinking. In my view, it is essential to consider both systemic thinking and question techniques. However, it is more crucial to listen attentively (listening to understand, not to reply) and to reinforce and develop the other person. They have done their best with the knowledge, perspectives, and reflections available to them at the time.

topic_description:
Welcome to a new week, this time with the theme of “Openness & Learning Mindset”, a basic mindset of curiosity and a willingness to be vulnerable and embrace change and grow. This competence is part of the IDG Being-Dimension.

We will reflect on the previous week, learn about the theme and plan the week ahead.
question:
Now look at your agenda for next week, what are the 3 things you want to learn for yourself? Think about the learning goals for this block and your assessment results.

Define 1 Action related to the theme of the week using the “take Action” button on the left bottom of this reflection that you will do each day this week to work towards these goals.

You could do one thing that is out of your comfort zone this week or something that you know you will not be good at, but you do it anyway, embracing the experience of learning rather than succeeding.

Or you could start a discussion about a topic that you are biased about. Listen actively to what the other person is saying and try to keep an open mind for their arguments.
suggestion_content: It's great to see you engaging with your learning goals! To deepen your reflection, consider exploring how your chosen actions will challenge you personally. What specific biases or discomforts do you anticipate facing, and how might embracing these experiences enhance your understanding?
final_reflection:
I want to learn projection mapping
Cinema 4D

topic_description:
Welcome to a new week, this time with the theme of “Inner Compass - Values”, a deeply felt sense of responsibility and commitment to values and purposes relating to the good of the whole. This competence is part of the IDG Being-Dimension.

Values are individual beliefs that motivate people to act one way or another. They serve as a guide for human behavior and inform our thoughts, words and actions.

We will reflect on the previous week, learn about the theme and plan the week ahead.

Why are there themed reflections?

Your innovative study program is aware of the importance of Inner Development in your Education and has decided to offer you Rflect to help you practice those Inner Competencies.

Inner Competences (some call it soft skills, personal development, etc.) are based on your thoughts, feelings, and behaviors. These competencies shape how we manage ourselves, relate to others, and respond to challenges. They are key to personal development, emotional well-being, and success in both personal and professional spheres. You can find out why there are important here.

Rflect helps you practice inner competencies outlined in the Inner Development Goals (IDG) and beyond.

Every week you will have one topic where you reflect on your personal learning journey and also on 1 of the 23 competencies outlined in the IDG Framework.

For the first semester(s) we will introduce those competencies broadly to you (with a few reflective questions). Later on, we will dive deeper into them and practice them with exercises and actions.

topic_description:
Welcome to a new week, this time with the theme of “Openness & Learning Mindset”, a basic mindset of curiosity and a willingness to be vulnerable and embrace change and grow. This competence is part of the IDG Being-Dimension.

We will reflect on the previous week, learn about the theme and plan the week ahead.
question: Reflect on a time when you had to step out of your comfort zone to learn something new or tackle a challenging task. How did your openness to vulnerability and change impact your learning and growth?
reflection_snapshot: Well, I think stepping out of my comfort zone was when I started making my last short film because I decided to save money for it instead of spending it on things for my own pleasure. Previously, I only saved money for travel, but this time, I spent almost a year putting money aside for the film. It was an amazing feeling to have some amount in my account—maybe not that much—but knowing that in the past, I would have definitely bought tickets and gone somewhere. Now, I am investing it in creativity. It really shaped me, and I feel that I have grown, that I made a sacrifice for the sake of art
suggestion_content: Great job on sharing your experience with stepping out of your comfort zone! It’s clear you’ve made a meaningful sacrifice for your art. topic_description:
We explore your ability to be focused, without judgement and in a state of open-ended presence.

Please note, whenever you reflect, formulate your thoughts in full sentences (and not only bullet points!).
question: What is your favorite way to clear your mind and stay focused when studying or attending classes? Do you feel you do this often enough? Why yes/no?
reflection_snapshot:
Je vais commencer par les moyens de rester concentrée en étudiant. Le premier étant de mettre à distance toute distraction sans pour autant m'interdire de pauses de temps à autres, c'est nécessaire pour que je sois efficace. Un moyen de rester concentrée aussi est celui d'écouter de la musique, il permet à mes pensées parasites de se taire et les remplacent par des mélodies et des paroles qui ne viennent pas de moi. 
En ce qui concerne les moments où je vais en cours, je dirais qu'un moyen de faire le vide dans ma tête et d'être concentrée est plutôt le fait de porter toute mon attention sur ce que dis le professeur en essayant d'avoir un minimum de distractions faciles d'accès proche de moi (que ça soit des applications sur mon pc ou bien des gens à côté de qui je suis assise et qui discutent). Ce n'est pas toujours facile de rester concentrée en classe, les périodes sont parfois plutôt longue et mon cerveau décroche à un moment ou à un autre. Une autre technique qui a tendance à fonctionner lorsque je suis en classe, est de dessiner en écoutant, je concentre mon énergie dans quelque chose de physique qui ne me demande aucune réflexion tout en écoutant ce que dis le professeur, je canalise en quelque sorte ma bougeotte en dessinant. 
Lorsque je suis concentrée, j'ai plutôt tendance à ne pas voir le temps passer, alors que lorsque je suis distraite, j'ai beaucoup plus conscience du temps et j'ai plus de facilités à m'ennuyer et à divaguer, penser à autre chose comme à ce que je vais faire en sortant de cours le soir, ce que je vais manger, etc. 
Je pense que l'effort que je fournis dans ma concentration dépend beaucoup des matières dans lesquelles je suis, et d'à quel point le prof fait ou a fait vivre son cours en nous l'expliquant, l'impression qu'ils me laissent impacte ma motivation à réussir du mieux que je peux.
suggestion_content: C'est super que tu partages tes stratégies pour rester concentrée en classe et en étudiant ! Pour approfondir ta réflexion, que dirais-tu d'explorer comment ces techniques influencent ton apprentissage à long terme ? Quelles émotions ressens-tu lorsque tu es concentrée par rapport à quand tu es distraite ?

question_clean: What is your favorite way to clear your mind and stay focused when studying or attending classes? Do you feel you do this often enough? Why yes/no?
reflection_snapshot_clean:
Je vais commencer par les moyens de rester concentrée en étudiant. Le premier étant de mettre à distance toute distraction sans pour autant m'interdire de pauses de temps à autres, c'est nécessaire pour que je sois efficace. Un moyen de rester concentrée aussi est celui d'écouter de la musique, il permet à mes pensées parasites de se taire et les remplacent par des mélodies et des paroles qui ne viennent pas de moi. 
En ce qui concerne les moments où je vais en cours, je dirais qu'un moyen de faire le vide dans ma tête et d'être concentrée est plutôt le fait de porter toute mon attention sur ce que dis le professeur en essayant d'avoir un minimum de distractions faciles d'accès proche de moi (que ça soit des applications sur mon pc ou bien des gens à côté de qui je suis assise et qui discutent). question: How can you recreate the state of flow that you have experienced in the past?
reflection_snapshot:
Le recréer dans mon appartement n'est pas si difficile, il faut seulement que j'en ai la motivation. Je Le recréer est assez simple, je vis seule, c'est donc parfait pour être au calme et j'arrive à me motiver plutôt bien pour commencer à travailler, après ce n'est qu'une question de le faire. Pour recréer cette atmosphère dans des lieux publics comme la bibliothèque, j'ai tendance à utiliser mes écouteurs, je mets des mélodies ou alors des playlists que j'aime, ou simplement je mets mes écouteurs en réduction de bruit sans musique et ça créer alors une sorte de casque anti-bruit qui fait un peu l'effet d'une bulle dans laquelle je me plonge. 
Je pense que ce qui déclenche réellement ma motivation est le fait de penser à ce que je peux accomplir si je réussis dans mes études, mes objectifs d'avenir me motivent beaucoup à m'impliquer. L'élément déclencheur précis est plus difficile à déterminer, je dirais sûrement lorsque je suis chez moi que c'est soit le ras-le-bol de ne rien faire ou de regarder des choses qui se ressemblent toujours et encore sur les réseaux sociaux, soit c'est parce que je me rends compte que tout n'est pas clair dans ce que j'ai fais dans la journée et je sens alors le besoin de trouver des réponses à mes questions.

topic_title: #4 + #5 Debrief on project proposals & preparing the interim presentation
question: What were the key learnings from the feedback you received from your coach? Did you resonate with the feedback? Now imagine playing devil's advocate: how would you argue against the feedback your coach gave you?
suggestion_content: Your reflection shows a solid start in engaging with the feedback from your coach, which is great! To deepen your reflection, consider exploring how the feedback specifically impacted your approach or mindset. What aspects of the feedback surprised you, and how might you apply it moving forward?
final_reflection: The feedback from our coach emphasized three key areas: the importance of collecting more data for relevant results, using new and recent sources, and ensuring clients or interviewees leave with added value by challenging them through insightful questions. I resonated with this feedback, especially the focus on data-driven insights and the need to stay current with information. However, more data isn’t always better, as sometimes quality outweighs quantity. Additionally, while recent sources are important, historical data can offer valuable context, and challenging clients too early might hinder rapport if not balanced with active listening.

question: Was waren für Dich 1-3 persönliche Highlights zum Start des CAS?
reflection_snapshot:
Der Austausch mit anderen Teilnehmenden, die ebenfalls Interesse an digitalen Lehr- und Lernkulturen haben, ist eine bereichernde Erfahrung. Auch die Diskussionen über gemeinsame Herausforderungen und Lösungen sowie Best Practices bietet wertvolle Einblicke und Ideen für die eigene Praxis.
Ein weiteres Highlight ist das Erkennen neuer Perspektiven auf Lernprozesse und der bewusste Umgang mit den unterschiedlichen Bedürfnissen der Lernenden in einer digitalen Welt.
Ein Highlight war für mich auch die Möglichkeit, gleich ein erstes kleines Projekt in Angriff zu nehmen und dieses mit drei anderen Teilnehmenden kollaborativ zusammenarbeiten. Es war spannend das theoretische Wissen anwenden zu können und gemeinsam eine Lektion zu entwickeln
suggestion_content: Es ist großartig zu sehen, wie engagiert du dich mit den anderen Teilnehmenden austauschst und neue Perspektiven auf Lernprozesse entdeckst! Was hat dich besonders überrascht oder inspiriert in diesen Diskussionen? Und wie kannst du die Erkenntnisse aus deinem Projekt in deiner zukünftigen Praxis konkret umsetzen?
final_reflection:

topic_title: #3&4 Peer Group Exercise: The role of a Coach (nicht Bewertugsrelevant)
topic_description:
In this exercise you will alternately take on the role of a coach to practice this important leadership skill.

Coaching is important because it empowers individuals to unlock their potential, facilitating personal and professional growth. It enhances communication skills, enabling more effective leadership and collaboration within teams. Additionally, coaching fosters a culture of continuous learning and development, leading to improved performance and job satisfaction.
question: What would you do differently next time? What questions would you ask to help your peers to come to their own insights and next steps?
reflection_snapshot:
I would try mainly two things:
1. Ask more specifically what they have already done.
2. Be more patient and not rushing to a solution.
suggestion_content: It's great to see you thinking critically about your approach! To deepen your reflection, consider how asking about their previous actions could lead to more meaningful discussions. What specific insights do you hope to gain from their experiences? How might patience change the dynamics of your conversations?
final_reflection:
I would try mainly two things:
1. Ask more specifically what they have already done.
2. Be more patient and not rushing to a solution.

I would ask questions that make them think and are direct enough to not lose their essence. Like this new ideas can emerge.

question: Consider your attitude toward feedback, whether it is from professors, peers, or your own self-assessment. How do you embrace constructive criticism and use it to enhance your learning and personal development, rather than taking it personally?
reflection_snapshot:
FEEDBACK PLEASE!

Note: As the word count is limited to around 300 words, this reflection will focus on feedback in relation to self-assessment. Over the past week, I have dedicated time to this topic, and I believe it is also related to my reaction when I receive feedback from others, which I often take personally.

I am my own worst critic. I often think I am not good enough for myself. In the past, I  didn't ask myself why I was criticising myself. I was of the opinion that a part of me is constantly trying to improve and develop, so I know this criticism also comes from this positive desire to better myself. One of my personal values is “quality”. This means for me: (always) giving the best, e.g. working flawlessly. It is already heading in the direction of perfectionism, which I have had to deal with since I was a child. I have consistently tried to suppress or silence my inner critic. However, the inner critic only gets louder, which is why I have decided to take action and have a discussion with it. During this inner discussion, I try to separate the reality from the thoughts and emphasise my positive qualities. I analyse the inner critic's arguments and look at them as objectively as possible in order to understand whether my inner critic wants to encourage and motivate me even more or whether it is just holding me back in my actions. 
My personal critic is currently focused on the Master's programme, as he believes it is too demanding and that I cannot achieve the required performance. I have already presented some convincing arguments to my inner critic (e.g. positive MC grades), but as soon as new challenging tasks have been assigned by the university, he returns with new arguments, meaning the discussion is still ongoing. The fact that I am engaging with this critical inner voice and its arguments has already given me a lot of self-confidence. I have also realised that I cannot expect myself to already meet the requirements of the Master's degree because I am here right now to learn certain hard and soft skills. I have to allow and give myself time, not only for my studies, but also for my personal growth, and I have to trust myself.
suggestion_content: You've done a great job of articulating your inner dialogue and the struggle with your inner critic. It’s clear that you’re on a journey of self-discovery and growth. To deepen your reflection, consider exploring how specific feedback from professors or peers has influenced your self-assessment. What strategies can you implement to view feedback as a tool for growth rather than a personal attack?

final_reflection_clean:
FEEDBACK PLEASE!

Note: As the word count is limited to around 300 words, this reflection will focus on feedback in relation to my own self-assessment. Over the past week, I have dedicated time to this topic, and I believe it is also related to my reaction when I receive feedback from others, which I often take personally.

I am my own worst critic. I often think I am not good enough for myself. In the past, I  didn't ask myself why I was criticising myself. I was of the opinion that a part of me is constantly trying to improve and develop, so I know this criticism also comes from this positive desire to better myself. One of my personal values is “quality”. This means for me: (always) giving the best, e.g. working flawlessly. It is already heading in the direction of perfectionism, which I have had to deal with since I was a child. I have consistently tried to suppress or silence my inner critic. However, the inner critic only gets louder, which is why I have decided to take action and have a discussion with it. During this inner discussion, I try to separate the reality from the thoughts and emphasise my positive qualities. I analyse the inner critic's arguments and look at them as objectively as possible in order to understand whether my inner critic wants to encourage and motivate me even more or whether it is just holding me back in my actions. 
My inner critic is currently focused on the Master's programme, as he believes it is too demanding and that I cannot achieve the required performance. I have already presented some convincing arguments to my inner critic (e.g. positive MC grades), but as soon as new challenging tasks have been assigned by the university, he returns with new arguments, meaning the discussion is still ongoing. The fact that I am engaging with this critical inner voice and its arguments has already given me a lot of self-confidence. I have also realised that I cannot expect myself to already meet the requirements of the Master's degree because I am here right now to learn certain hard and soft skills. I have to allow and give myself time, not only for my studies, but also for my personal growth, and I have to trust myself.

topic_title: Week #5 Start the week: Learning Mindset
topic_description:
Welcome to a new week, this time with the theme of “Learning Mindest”, which means having a basic mindset of curiosity and a willingness to be vulnerable and embrace change and grow.

A capacity to be open to learning, reevaluation and be curious about alternative ways of perceiving and interpreting various issues requires a self that has a considerable measure of robustness. If one's sense of self-regard is dependent on identification with a certain self-image or if one's sense of safety is linked to a need to defend a certain set of beliefs and values, there is probably a need for having psychological defense mechanisms that might inhibit the capacity for remaining open and curious when encountering unfamiliar or diverging views or events. Openness and a learning mindset is therefore not to be regarded solely as a skill that can be trained, but is intimately linked to adult development processes involving the whole self. Openness is also one of the personality traits included in the Big Five framework.
question:
Now look at your agenda for this week, what are the 3 things you want to learn for yourself? Think about the learning goals for this block and your assessment results.
What are 3 things your group wants to achieve this week?

Define 1 Action related to the theme of the week using the “take Action” button on the left bottom of this reflection that you will do each day this week to work towards these goals.

You could do one thing that is out of your comfort zone this week or something that you know you will not be good at, but you do it anyway, embracing the experience of learning rather than succeeding.

Or you could start a discussion about a topic that you are biased about. Listen actively to what the other person is saying and try to keep an open mind for their arguments.

topic_description:
Dear Student,

Welcome to the Rflect journey that will accompany your Capstone project!

You are invited to go on this journey in order to help you personalize the learning experience more, and make sure you get the most out of it for your own learning, rather than doing it ‘just’ to pass the course. You will train key future skills such as self-awareness, metacognition and coaching which are in key demand for any future profession.

Your reflections will not be graded, but you are required to complete at least 80% of the questions and answer in a serious way. Even though nobody can read the reflections marked ‘private’, Rflect tracks numerous statistics for your lecturer such as number of characters and time spent per question. The goal is not to maximize these numbers, but to do it ‘normally’. From experience we can tell that the more honest you are with yourself, the better your learning outcomes will be.

You receive questions in English, but you can answer in either German or English.

All the best!

topic_description:
Dear Student,

Welcome to the Rflect journey that will accompany your Capstone project!

You are invited to go on this journey in order to help you personalize the learning experience more, and make sure you get the most out of it for your own learning, rather than doing it ‘just’ to pass the course. You will train key future skills such as self-awareness, metacognition and coaching which are in key demand for any future profession.

Your reflections will not be graded, but you are required to complete at least 80% of the questions and answer in a serious way. Even though nobody can read the reflections marked ‘private’, Rflect tracks numerous statistics for your lecturer such as number of characters and time spent per question. The goal is not to maximize these numbers, but to do it ‘normally’. From experience we can tell that the more honest you are with yourself, the better your learning outcomes will be.

You receive questions in English, but you can answer in either German or English.

All the best!

topic_description:
Welcome to a new week, this time with the theme of “Co-Creation”, the skills and motivation to build, develop and facilitate collaborative relationships with diverse stake-holders, characterised by psychological safety and genuine co-creation. This competence is part of the IDG Collaboration-Dimension.

We will reflect on the previous week, learn about the theme and plan the week ahead.
question:
Now look at your agenda for next week, what are the 3 things you want to learn for yourself? Think about the learning goals for this block and your assessment results.

Define 1 Action related to the theme of the week using the “take Action” button on the left bottom of this reflection that you will do each day this week to work towards these goals.

Looking at your group project in BFH or at your work you could for example:

  • actively work on building trust within the team by respecting each other’s ideas, providing constructive feedback, and acknowledging contributions.

  • identify and involve a diverse group of stakeholders, including team members, potential customers, or community members. Ensure everyone has a voice in the process.

question: What 1-3 things did you learn this week that you would like to remember? This can be something you learned in class, about yourself or a Meta-learning, etc.
reflection_snapshot:
J'ai observé que j'avais tendance à remettre à demain le travail pour les matières où j'ai de la peine. Guidée par une personne, j'ai trouvé la motivation de m'organiser pour travailler tous les jours un petit moment sur ces matières.

J'ai appris que la collaboration et l'organisation sont des éléments importants pour entretenir les lien d'une famille.
suggestion_content: C'est super que tu aies pris conscience de ta tendance à procrastiner et que tu aies trouvé une méthode pour t'organiser ! Tu as bien identifié des apprentissages, mais il manque un peu de profondeur sur tes émotions et l'impact de ces leçons. Que penses-tu de l'importance de la collaboration dans d'autres aspects de ta vie ? Comment cela a-t-il changé ta perspective ?
final_reflection:
J'ai observé que j'avais tendance à remettre à demain le travail pour les matières où j'ai de la peine. Cela me décourageait gentiment. Guidée par une personne, j'ai trouvé la motivation de m'organiser pour travailler tous les jours un petit moment sur ces matières. Mettre en place cette organisation me redonne de la confiance.

question: Think about your current group challenge or a group project at work. What role did you take in the group? Is this the role you usually take?
reflection_snapshot:
I see myself as somewhat the "leader" of the group, maybe the term "coordinator" would match me better. 
Not always but I have taken this role in several groups over time and it is how I feel most successfull. Maybe it's just that I have a problem with losing control. However, when I know that I don't understand the topic well or that others are clearly more in the topic or have better ideas (in my view), I have no problem standing back.
suggestion_content: You've done a great job reflecting on your role in the group and your feelings about leadership. It’s insightful that you recognize when to step back. How does your desire for control influence your interactions with others in the group? Have you noticed any specific outcomes when you let others take the lead?
final_reflection:
I see myself as somewhat the "leader" of the group, maybe the term "coordinator" would match me better. 
Not always but I have taken this role in several groups over time and it is how I feel most successfull. Maybe it's just that I have a problem with losing control. However, when I know that I don't understand the topic well or that others are clearly more in the topic or have better ideas (in my view), I have no problem standing back. 
I have made the experience that, when ideas I was really sure they were good, but a group decided to not take my way, I had difficulties still giving my best.

question: Are you working with people that you are already familiar with or entirely new people? Why have you chosen that setup? What are (dis)-advantages of this constellation?
reflection_snapshot: We have chosen a hybrid model:
suggestion_content: It's great that you've chosen a hybrid model for your group work! To enhance your reflection, delve deeper into the emotions and thoughts you experienced while working with familiar versus new people. This will help you articulate the advantages and disadvantages more vividly and personally.
final_reflection:
We have chosen a hybrid team model for our Capstone project: Our team consists of two independent groups of friends who coordinated beforehand to select the project together, and we added a sixth member during the first lesson.

Benefits of Working with Friends:
1. Increased Accountability: Knowing some of the team members beforehand enhances accountability and, consequently, reliability within the group.
2. Higher Trust Levels: There is a greater sense of trust, as team members are confident that those they know will deliver high-quality work.
3. Enjoyment: Working with friends makes the experience more enjoyable and fosters a positive team atmosphere.

Benefits of Combining Two Friend Groups:
1. Diverse Skill Sets: Combining two separate friend groups allows team members to get to know new people with different skills and strengths.
2. Balanced Approach: It reduces the risk of approaching tasks too casually, as working with a mix of familiar and unfamiliar people encourages a more professional mindset.

Benefits of Including a Completely New Member:
1. New Perspectives: Introducing a new, unknown person to the group brings fresh ideas and perspectives, which can prevent groupthink and encourage innovative problem-solving.
2. Meeting New People: It’s a great chance to get to know someone completely new and mix things up a bit.

Disadvantages of This Setup:
1. Time-Consuming Coordination: Combining multiple friend groups and adding a new person requires additional time to align expectations and goals. We had at least three meetings before the Capstone even started to ensure everyone was on the same page.
2. Complex Scheduling: Managing different schedules and availability across a diverse group requires more time and effort for coordination.

topic_title: Week #5 Start the week: Learning Mindset
topic_description:
Welcome to a new week, this time with the theme of “Learning Mindest”, which means having a basic mindset of curiosity and a willingness to be vulnerable and embrace change and grow.

A capacity to be open to learning, reevaluation and be curious about alternative ways of perceiving and interpreting various issues requires a self that has a considerable measure of robustness. If one's sense of self-regard is dependent on identification with a certain self-image or if one's sense of safety is linked to a need to defend a certain set of beliefs and values, there is probably a need for having psychological defense mechanisms that might inhibit the capacity for remaining open and curious when encountering unfamiliar or diverging views or events. Openness and a learning mindset is therefore not to be regarded solely as a skill that can be trained, but is intimately linked to adult development processes involving the whole self. Openness is also one of the personality traits included in the Big Five framework.
question:
Now look at your agenda for this week, what are the 3 things you want to learn for yourself? Think about the learning goals for this block and your assessment results.
What are 3 things your group wants to achieve this week?

Define 1 Action related to the theme of the week using the “take Action” button on the left bottom of this reflection that you will do each day this week to work towards these goals.

You could do one thing that is out of your comfort zone this week or something that you know you will not be good at, but you do it anyway, embracing the experience of learning rather than succeeding.

Or you could start a discussion about a topic that you are biased about. Listen actively to what the other person is saying and try to keep an open mind for their arguments.

topic_description:
Welcome to a new week, this time with the theme of “Openness & Learning Mindset”, a basic mindset of curiosity and a willingness to be vulnerable and embrace change and grow. This competence is part of the IDG Being-Dimension.

We will reflect on the previous week, learn about the theme and plan the week ahead.
question: Reflect on a time when you had to step out of your comfort zone to learn something new or tackle a challenging task. How did your openness to vulnerability and change impact your learning and growth?
reflection_snapshot: Ich habe sehr Mühe mit den Mathematik Übungsserien und muss mir Hilfe holen. Auch dann sitze ich lange an den Aufgaben und es fällt mir sehr schwer nicht zu versweifeln und aufzugeben. Trotz dem Gefühl aufgeben zu wollen, Stelle ich mich den Aufgaben und versuche mein bestes. Ich lerne dabei, damit zufrieden zu sein, dass ich Arbeite, auch wenn ich noch keine Erfolge spüre. Ich werde schnell frustriert und überfordert, was mir nicht Hilft beim Lernen, da mein Gehirn blockiert, ich den ganzen Körper verspanne und mich elend fühle. Ich muss an diesem Thema arbeiten, damit ich nicht so schnell in Stress komme, sobald ich etwas nicht gut kann.
suggestion_content: Es ist toll zu sehen, wie du dich den Herausforderungen in der Mathematik stellst und trotz der Schwierigkeiten dranbleibst. Du hast die Gefühle der Frustration und Überforderung gut beschrieben, aber es fehlt etwas an der Reflexion über die konkreten Lernprozesse. Wie könntest du deine Strategien anpassen, um mit dem Stress besser umzugehen? Was hast du aus dieser Erfahrung über dich selbst gelernt?
final_reflection: Ich habe sehr Mühe mit den Mathematik Übungsserien und muss mir Hilfe holen. Auch dann sitze ich lange an den Aufgaben und es fällt mir sehr schwer nicht zu versweifeln und aufzugeben. Trotz dem Gefühl aufgeben zu wollen, Stelle ich mich den Aufgaben und versuche mein bestes. Ich lerne dabei, damit zufrieden zu sein, dass ich Arbeite, auch wenn ich noch keine Erfolge spüre. Ich werde schnell frustriert und überfordert, was mir nicht Hilft beim Lernen, da mein Gehirn blockiert, ich den ganzen Körper verspanne und mich elend fühle. Ich muss an diesem Thema arbeiten, damit ich nicht so schnell in Stress komme, sobald ich etwas nicht gut kann.
